races versus reflection. Tests in Graal can often reflect their own methods, and JUnit seems to register these methods within its configuration. However, it might not include nested samples or constructors from inner classes. So, there’s a bit to sort through!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_y0Ur6qE74l2ZtVmvoZeuhvdW|fc_033ad2ee07d372680169f663fa2e148195a45d42478fd08967", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src -path '*/src/test/resources/*' -type f | head -50 && find tests/src/io.lettuce/lettuce-core/6.2.6.RELEASE -type f | sort | grep -E 'native-image|reflect|resource'"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 981, "output": 1027, "cacheRead": 34816, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 36824, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777755114924, "responseId": "resp_033ad2ee07d372680169f663eb607481959a20dc87519405bd"}}
